    <note>Zhao(1) Yong [3216] Qian Gu, Wudu wencui xuji (SKQSZB), 38.19b-21a (2nd wife, born Fang(1), who died in 1241 at age 72), 38.25b-27a (concerns the kindred alliance between the Fang(1) and Zhao(1). Yong's first wife, born Wang(2) [same surname as mother] died in 1191. His first daughter married Yang(2) Ze (not in dataset) and then remarried Yao Ziyin (not in dataset) [who was probably kin of Zicai (not in dataset), a Fuzhou, Houguan jinshi in 1199] although Zicai's elder brother, Yourong (not in dataset), uses a different generational indicator in his mingzi. The annotation to Yong's funerary inscription in Jiangsu jin, 14.37b cites several examples of widow remarriage in Song and discusses how there was no taboo during Song against widow remarriage. Yong's funerary inscription identifies his grandfather as Qingsun, whereas documentation for father, Si [24288], makes his grandfather, Xiaosun [24287]. CBD mis-identifies Xiaosun's father as Xiao. Jiangsu jin, 14.35b-38a. CBD, 4, 3319-20.</note>
